    "key": "d2fac960-2e7d-41b4-ac2a-4c86296a3e4b",
    "name": "Overview",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Overview",
    "content": "<p>I was born in 1965 in Kirkcaldy (Fife) and was educated at the local Catholic schools. I left Scotland aged 17 to attend Maynooth College (Ireland) and graduated in 1987. After some years travelling and working abroad I returned to Scotland to complete a Doctorate in Social Anthropology at Edinburgh University (1997-2002) on the topic of Scottish Nationalism.</p>\n<p>I was Research Fellow at Glasgow University (2006-2008) before being appointed Lecturer in Sociology at QMU in 2008 and Senior lecturer in 2014. I was Programme Leader for the Psychology &amp; Sociology programme (2010-2014) and during this time helped to successfully launch the new single honours programme in Public Sociology at QMU.</p>\n<p>Since 2017 I have co-convened the BSA Scottish Sociology study group. In 2021/2022 I was Senior Visiting Fellow at Mathias Corvinus Collegium (Budapest).</p>\n<p><strong>Affiliations/Memberships to Other Organisations:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>British Sociological Association</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Research/Knowledge Exchange Centre Membership:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>An associate member of the <a data-id=\"1265\" href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/9e59330129ac41028d861633fdcb6a2d}\" title=\"Centre for Applied Social Sciences\">Centre for Applied Social Sciences</a></li>\n</ul>"
  },
  {
    "key": "c51d23f1-f387-4bcf-be73-a7d74b9cfee7",
    "name": "Research Interests",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Research Interests",
    "content": "<p><strong>Active research interests:</strong></p>\n<p>Ethnography, Social Class, Nationalism, Sociology of Christianity, Sociology of Scotland, Pilgrimage</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Research Methods:</strong></p>\n<p>Ethnography, Interviewing, Longitudinal Research</p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "f9fb5ac0-335a-4c0b-be08-13c7ecbdf96a",
    "name": "Research Publications",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Research Publications",
    "content": "<p><a rel=\"noopener\" href=\"https://eresearch.qmu.ac.uk/browse?type=author&amp;value=Gilfillan%2C+Paul\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Dr Paul Gilfillan - eResearch Repository QMU\" data-anchor=\"?type=author&amp;value=Gilfillan%2C+Paul\"><span class=\"blue-btn\">Dr Paul Gilfillan research publications and outputs (QMU eResearch profile)</span></a></p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "25ebc429-0fdb-4e30-9fb0-636b33fdee88",
    "name": "Funded Projects",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Funded Projects",
    "content": ""
  },
  {
    "key": "7747755d-d177-4565-80b8-4bec7b46eac7",
    "name": "Teaching & Learning",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Teaching & Learning ",
    "content": "<p>My main areas of teaching are Introduction to Academic Life, Research Methods, the history of social theory, the sociology of contemporary Scotland.</p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "06a62d65-45fc-40cf-bb6b-bad75f4e5ffe",
    "name": "Activities & Awards",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Activities & Awards ",
    "content": "<p><span class=\"lead\">Awards:</span></p>\n<p>I was nominated for the 2014 BSA Philip Abrams Memorial Prize for best first sole-authored monograph in sociology.</p>\n<p>Senior Research Fellow, <em>Mathias Corvinus Collegium</em> (Budapest); Sept. 2021-February 2022.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span class=\"lead\"><strong>Activities: </strong></span></p>\n<p><strong>MCC Podcast:</strong> <a rel=\"noopener\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lGrrCqz9IWU\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Patriotism and religion in education - Huub Ruël and Paul Gilfillan\" data-anchor=\"?v=lGrrCqz9IWU\">Patriotism and religion in education - Huub Ruël and Paul Gilfillan</a></p>\n<p><strong>Podcast:</strong> <a rel=\"noopener\" href=\"https://danubeinstitute.hu/en/podcast/paul-gilfillan-on-courage-and-humility-in-the-modern-university?fbclid=IwAR09Rcp1z9rm-CU7L8Gs8pgr2sAWVSJpnnr5oKEd57iEfbDYsYa9Ps5N8vY#.YjJbOoCEz8k.facebook\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Paul Gilfillan on courage and humility in the modern university\">Paul Gilfillan on Courage and Humility in the Modern University</a></p>\n<p><strong>MCC Article:</strong> <a rel=\"noopener\" href=\"https://mcc.hu/hir/dr-paul-gilfillan-a-skot-es-az-angol-katolicizmus-21-szazadi-alakulasarol?fbclid=IwAR07AtRjOfrITNg1ACPgnM2e5umotOVwKEl4QCVwazSJsDY3VnElbfdGYW4\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Lunch Talks - Paul Gilfillan\" data-anchor=\"?fbclid=IwAR07AtRjOfrITNg1ACPgnM2e5umotOVwKEl4QCVwazSJsDY3VnElbfdGYW4\">Lunch Talks</a></p>\n<p><strong>Mandiner Podcast:</strong> <a rel=\"noopener\" href=\"https://mandiner.hu/cikk/20220315_paul_gilfillan_skocia?fbclid=IwAR0zZz2Ui8nwxburwlq7ORgKxu6x01rdRhtpd4tAddZP7F5ueDlqK9_g-Vc\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Paul Gilfillan a Mandinernek\" data-anchor=\"?fbclid=IwAR0zZz2Ui8nwxburwlq7ORgKxu6x01rdRhtpd4tAddZP7F5ueDlqK9_g-Vc\">Paul Gilfillan a Mandinernek</a></p>\n<p><strong>Corvinak Article:</strong> <a rel=\"noopener\" href=\"https://corvinak.hu/velemeny/2022/01/31/a-skot-oktatas-visszaallitasa-sajat-tengelyere?fbclid=IwAR3yyrStPNwD5TL67ock87wCZ9PqxAjXLhf_YVSV-so3qynOyWYIgqK3QI4\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Corvinak Article: Restoring Scottish education onto its own axis\" data-anchor=\"?fbclid=IwAR3yyrStPNwD5TL67ock87wCZ9PqxAjXLhf_YVSV-so3qynOyWYIgqK3QI4\">Restoring Scottish education onto its own axis</a></p>\n<p><strong>MCC Conference Budapest:</strong> <a rel=\"noopener\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/MCC.Budapest/photos/gm.885139705724138/10159817914778524\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Photo Gallery - MCC Budapest\">Photo Gallery</a></p>\n<p><strong>MCC Conference Budapest:</strong> <a rel=\"noopener\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/MCC.Budapest/posts/10159848173003524\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Photo Gallery 2 - Budapest MCC Conference\">Photo Gallery 2 </a></p>\n<p><strong>MCC Conference Budapest:</strong> <a rel=\"noopener\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/MCC.Budapest/posts/10159831696448524\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Photo Gallery 3 - MCC Conference Budapest\">Photo Gallery 3</a> </p>\n<p> </p>"
